  "title" : "How do I get the current index/key in a &quot;for each&quot; loop",
  "body" : "<p>In Java, how do I get the index of the current element?</p>\n<pre><code>for (Element song: question){\n    song.currentIndex();         //&lt;&lt;want the current index\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>In PHP, you could do this:</p>\n<pre><code>foreach ($arr as $index =&gt; $value) {\n    echo &quot;Key: $index; Value: $value&quot;;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
